DDL(Data Definition Language) 
SQL commands that are used to define the structure of the database objects
--CREATE   = Create Database, and its tables, columns and indexes
--Alter    = Alter the structure of the database objects - add or remove columns, indexes, etc
--Drop     = delete tables.Indexes and even entire database.
--Rename   = rename a table
--Truncate = Clear out the contents of a table. Effectivelu the same as deleting and re-recreating the table.

DML(Data Manipulation Language)
SQL commands that are used to manipulate the data
--Select   = Query the database to retrieve rows of data
--Insert   = Insert data into a table
--Update   = Change the data in columns of a table 
--Delete   = Delete rows in a table
